cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper discusses a machine learning algorithm, specifically the Extreme Learning Machine (ELM), which is commonly used in the fields of neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes an improved algorithm, which involves selecting input weights and biases, indicating a focus on optimization and numerical methods, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of ELM in classification and regression applications, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the experimental results and performance of the algorithm, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
